definition: to walk in in a line
to pierce through/to pass through/to be stringed together/string of 1000 cash
and/as well as/and so/but (not)/yet (not)/(indicates causal relation)/(indicates change of state)/(indicates contrast)
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]

sentences.english: The students filed in the classroom.
A group of students filed in, fourteen or fifteen all told.
sentences.chinese: 一隊學生魚貫而入，共有十四五個人。

sentences.english: Hearing the sound of the engine, passengers file in the bus. And the cicerone does the nose-count again.
sentences.chinese: 聽到車子發動的聲音，旅客們又魚貫而入了。
